{{doc/start}}
Lua module that renders achievement tables from [[Module:Data/Achievements]] for the [[Achievements]] wiki page. Each achievement type has a dedicated exported function returning a sortable wikitable (without a heading), so the Achievements page can arrange section headings and editorial notes around them.

== Data source ==
Achievement data comes from [[Module:Data/Achievements]], which is auto-generated by running:
<pre>foundry_parser generate-lua</pre>
from the game installation at <code>F:\SteamLibrary\SteamApps\common\FOUNDRY</code>. Do not edit the data module directly.

== Usage on the Achievements page ==
Each section invokes its dedicated function:

<pre>
== Item Creation ==
{{#invoke:Achievements|item_creation}}

== Building Placement ==
{{#invoke:Achievements|building_built}}

== Research ==
{{#invoke:Achievements|research}}

== Lifetime Earnings ==
{{#invoke:Achievements|lifetime_earnings}}

== Market Dominance ==
{{#invoke:Achievements|market_dominance}}

== Space Station ==
{{#invoke:Achievements|space_station}}

== Quests ==
{{#invoke:Achievements|quests}}

== Special ==
{{#invoke:Achievements|fixed}}

{{#invoke:Achievements|remaining}}
</pre>

== Exported functions ==

{| class="wikitable"
! Function !! Achievement type !! Extra columns
|-
| <code>p.item_creation</code> || <code>MULTI_ITEMCREATION</code> || Item(s), Required count
|-
| <code>p.building_built</code> || <code>MULTI_BUILDINGBUILT</code> || Building(s), Required count
|-
| <code>p.research</code> || <code>MULTI_RESEARCH</code> || Research entries required
|-
| <code>p.lifetime_earnings</code> || <code>LIFETIME_EARNINGS</code> || Earnings required (Firmarlite Bars)
|-
| <code>p.market_dominance</code> || <code>MARKET_DOMINANCE</code> || Planets required
|-
| <code>p.space_station</code> || <code>SPACE_STATION</code> || Space Station upgrade
|-
| <code>p.quests</code> || <code>QUESTS</code> || Quest(s)
|-
| <code>p.fixed</code> || <code>FIXED</code> || (none — description only)
|-
| <code>p.remaining</code> || Any unhandled type || Heading + table rendered automatically
|}

== Notes ==
* All tables are sortable (<code>class="wikitable sortable"</code>).
* Achievements within each table are sorted by <code>sortOrder</code>, then alphabetically by display name.
* <code>p.remaining()</code> renders a heading and table for any achievement types added in future game updates that are not yet covered by a dedicated function. Place it at the bottom of the Achievements page to ensure new types are never silently omitted.
* Item, building, and research references are wikilinked by display name.
{{doc/end}}
